Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Halve the @green pepper{1} and discard the core and
seeds. Slice into thin strips, chop the strips into 3 pieces widthways. Peel and
grate the @garlic clove{1}. Zest and halve the @lime{½}. Drain and rinse the
@red kidney beans{1} in a #colander{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a medium #saucepan{} on medium high heat. Once hot,
add the garlic and half the @Mexican style spice mix{1}. Stir and cook for
~{1%minute}.

Pour the @water{240%ml} for the bulgur wheat into the saucepan with the garlic
and spice. Bring to the boil. Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%g}, kidney beans and
@chicken stock powder{1}, bring back up to the boil and simmer for
~{1%minute}. Pop a lid on the pan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side
for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Once
the pan is hot, add the green pepper and @diced chicken thigh{210%g}, season
with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Stir fry until the pepper has softened
and browned, and the chicken is browned and cooked through, ~{7-10%minutes}.

> TIP: Only stir a few times in order to get some colour on the pepper and
> chicken.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the pepper and chicken are cooked, add the remaining Mexican spice, lime
zest and @honey{15%g} to the pan. Stir together and cook until the honey has
caramelised and darkened slightly, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

Add a squeeze of lime to the bulgur, then fluff it up with a #fork{}. Taste and
season with salt and pepper if you feel it needs it. Spoon into #bowls{} and
top with the chicken and pepper pieces. Top with a spoonful of
@Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g} and a grind of pepper. Serve with the
remaining lime cut into wedges alongside. Enjoy!